{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure is typically at local module handoff (diff extraction -> review-input builder). A unit test of one parser function is too narrow; an in-process wiring test with fixture diffs catches leakage of unchanged lines. Rejected System because behavior text does not require real network/OS/subprocess, only correct local scoping logic.","test_description":"Run an in-process test wiring diff-reader output into review-input assembly using realistic unified diff fixtures; assert only changed hunks are present in the payload and unchanged file regions are excluded.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Diff-position correctness depends on real GitHub PR review API contract/semantics. Mocks can accept invalid positions and hide real failures (MOCK-HIDE). Rejected Agentic/Workflow because correctness here is API positioning, not model judgment.","test_description":"Against a real test PR, post inline comments using computed positions, then read back review threads via API and verify each comment appears on the intended file/hunk/line in PR diff context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pass/fail depends on real LLM output quality (finding a real bug). Deterministic stubs would always pass/fail and cannot validate model judgment. Rejected Workflow because behavior specifies one identification outcome, not multiple agentic decisions chained.","test_description":"Run the real model on a PR fixture with a known introduced defect; assert at least one returned finding correctly points to that defect class/location within acceptance tolerance over repeated trials.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to a posted inline comment ID from the same run.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is local state/wiring integrity between inline-post results and summary composer. In-process integration test catches ID mismatches/cross-run contamination. Rejected System because real network is not required to reproduce mapping bug; rejected Agentic because no dependence on model output quality.","test_description":"Execute posting-orchestration modules with deterministic finding fixtures and fake API responses containing comment IDs; assert summary payload references only IDs returned in that run and every summary entry maps to one posted inline comment.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"No inline finding is dropped from the final summary payload before posting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a pipeline handoff/completeness invariant across local modules (collector -> summarizer -> payload builder). Unit tests per function can miss cross-module dropping. Rejected System/Agentic because no real OS/network/model-output dependency is required to expose drop logic.","test_description":"Run end-to-end in-process assembly from inline finding list to summary payload with varied fixture sizes/order; assert cardinality and identity preservation (set equality) before post call.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"The automation sequence (read diff, post inline comments, post summary) succeeds for a real pull request when provided a fixed precomputed finding set.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires success on a real PR and real posting sequence, so real external API/network contract is the failure boundary. Rejected Agentic because findings are fixed/precomputed (no model-judgment dependence). Rejected Workflow because no multi-agentic chain is required.","test_description":"Execute the automation against a real test PR using a fixed finding fixture; verify diff retrieval, inline comment creation, and summary comment posting all complete with expected API-visible artifacts.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.03,"System":0.94,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"The full live run with model-generated findings (read diff, analyze, post inline comments, post summary) completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"This is a full agent pipeline with at least one real model decision plus downstream actions on real external systems; failures can emerge from cross-step agentic-to-system handoff. By definition, this is beyond single-step Agentic. Rejected lower levels because they cannot expose combined pipeline failures under live model variability and real PR API behavior.","test_description":"Run the entire live pipeline on a real test PR: fetch diff, generate findings with real model, post inline comments, then post summary; assert completion, artifact consistency, and no manual retries/intervention.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.0,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.22,"Workflow":0.7}}]}
